Revision Sheet for C#



All the functions having brackets () at the end are methods, else are properties
Eg: toUpper() is method, .Exists is a property

String methods
length : s.Length
uppercase: toUpper()
lowercase: toLower()
check substring: s.contains(s1)
find index of i: s.IndexOf("rohan")

find a substring part: s.SubString(x,len) how much characters from x  , s.SubString(x) (all characters after x)

Math functions

Math.Abs(-x) : +x
Math.Pow(x,y): x^y
Math.Sqrt(x): root(x)
Math.Max(x,y)
Math.Min(x,y)

Take input:
Use Console.ReadLine()
int x = Console.ReadLine()
Output: Console.WriteLine()
Line adds a new line so if we don't want to go to new line don't use Line
Console.Write("Enter a number");
int x=Console.ReadLine();


Type Coversion:
int num=Convert.ToInt32("x") (toInt64, toDouble are the other options )
double num1=Convert.ToDouble("x");


User Input + Type Coversion
int x=Convert.ToInt32(Console.ReadLine());



Arrays:
1D
int []a;
int []a= new int[n];

2D:
int[] colors=new int[1,2,3];
int[] colors=new int[1][2][3];


Methods:
// Array.method() all these methods are a part of Array Class
    Length(arr)
    IndexOf(arr,x)
    Clear(arr,x,y)
    Copy(arr,arr1,x,y) || Copy(arr,arr1,x)
    Sort()
    Reverse()


List : Dynamic Size
var numbers = new List<int>();
List<int> ls=new List<int>();
Methods:
    Add()
    AddRange()
    Remove()
    RemoveAt()
    IndexOf()
    LastIndexOf(i)
    Contains() 
    Count (alternate of length)

// forEach 
forEach(var i in nums)
{
    System.Console.WriteLine(i);
}

Data and Time Methods : https://www.javatpoint.com/datetime-in-c-sharp
    Date.Now
    Date.Today


File methods
Copy file x into y: File.Copy(x,y);
Delte a file :File.Delete(x);
check existence:File.Exists(x)
var x=File.ReadAllText(x);
(x and y are the path of the file)
